Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine buff-brown; mixed inclusions. Circula stamp with rose symbol, stamped on turn.
Curator's comments: Name Soteridas. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0014.18.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0349)
